{"word":"αἰσχύνω","slug":"αἰσχύνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰσχύνω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make ugly, disfigure, mar</i>, <el>πρόσωπον, κόμην</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in moral sense, <i>to dishonour, tarnish</i>, <el>γένος πατέρων</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to dishonour</i> a woman, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li250'><b>B. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be dishonoured</i>, <el>νέκυς ᾐσχυμμένος</el>, of Patroclus, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to be ashamed, feel shame</i>, <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be ashamed at</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; and with Preps., <el>αἰσχ. ἐπί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <el>ἔν τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>ὑπέρ τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> part <i>to be ashamed at doing</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—but <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to be ashamed to do</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to feel shame before one</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}